## üîê Secret Types Explained

### GITHUB_APP_SECRET vs INTERNAL_APP_SECRET
- **`GITHUB_APP_SECRET`**: This is the webhook secret from your GitHub App settings. Your Next.js app uses this to verify that incoming webhooks are actually from GitHub (not from attackers).

- **`INTERNAL_APP_SECRET`**: This is a secret you create yourself. Your GitHub Actions use this when making webhook calls to your Next.js app, so your app can verify the requests are from your own CI/CD pipeline.

**Security Flow:**
1. GitHub ‚Üí Your App: Uses `GITHUB_APP_SECRET` for verification
2. GitHub Actions ‚Üí Your App: Uses `INTERNAL_APP_SECRET` for authentication

